<P>
   COLLEGE FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FIESTA _ Is Tennessee a team of destiny? Will Florida State,
like Florida in 1996, win a national championship thanks to the
hand of Fate? Those are just two of the questions to be answered in
the Fiesta Bowl on Jan. 4. Tennessee has dodged some bullets this
season but have always found a way to win. They lost Jamal Lewis on
Oct. 5 and still found a way to win. Tennessee has certainly had
more talented teams than this one but this group could give the
Vols their first national championship since 1951. Florida State
was convinced it was out of the national championship race when it
lost to N.C. State. But 10 straight wins plus some luck have put
the Seminoles into position to win their second national
championship in this decade (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16-18. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATORS-SPURRIER _ The last time the Gators played in the
Orange Bowl, someone named Steve Spurrier was the QB. We look back
at that game and at Spurrier's games there as a pro with Niners.
(Dolch, Palm Beach Post) WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
