<P>
   CRIME-DECLINE (Boston) _ The number of people robbed in 1997
dropped a stunning 17 percent, the Justice Department reported
Sunday. That is not only good news, but, criminologists say,
provides an important clue that the main factors behind the decline
in crime over the past seven years may be the withering away of the
crack cocaine market and police efforts to seize handguns from
criminals and juveniles. By Fox Butterfield.
