<SLUG> BC-OBIT-KAMINSTEIN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MERWIN KAMINSTEIN, 63, RETAIL EXECUTIVE 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Mass., Fla., N.H., Ga., Pa.)  (lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Merwin Kaminstein, a former retail executive, died on Dec. 21 at
Massachusetts General Hospital in Boston. Kaminstein, a resident of
Boston and Bonita Springs, Fla., was 63.
</P>
<P>
   The cause was cancer, said his niece, Gail Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   Kaminstein headed several department-store companies starting in
1971, when he became president of Donaldson's, part of Allied
Department Stores. From 1976 to 1979, he was president of another
Allied store chain, Jordan Marsh. He also served as president of
Filene's and Rich's department stores, both owned by Federated
Department Stores, between 1979 and 1987.
</P>
<P>
   In 1990, after two years in the real-estate industry, Kaminstein
was named chairman and chief executive at Brookstone, a chain of
specialty stores based in Nashua, N.H. He retired as chief
executive in 1995.
</P>
<P>
   After graduating from Hofstra University in 1956, Kaminstein
began his career in retail at Abraham &AMP; Straus in New York, worked
at Federated's headquarters in New York from 1967 to 1971 and then
joined Donaldson's.
</P>
<P>
   Kaminstein is survived by his wife, Janet, of Boston and Bonita
Springs; two daughters, Susan Street of Atlanta and Ann, of
Washington; two sons, Greg, of New Boston, N.H., and Steve, of
Noxen, Pa.; a sister, Nancy Tulis of Atlanta, and four
grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
