<P>
   FBN-RHODEN-COLUMN (Phiadelphia) _ Commentary from the
Giants-Eagles game. By William C. Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-ISLES-LACHANCE (Sunrise, Fla.) _ There are games when Scott
Lachance is outstanding, when he flashes the skills and instincts
that, for years, have made him one of the Islanders most reliable
defenseman. But Lachance's play has declined so much recently that
the Islanders coach and general manager has scratched him three
times and said publicly that Lachance has lost his spot on the
team. By Tarik El-Bashir.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-COLLEGE-RACERS (Charlotte, N.C.) _ From its beginnings in
the hollows of North Carolina as a cat-and-mouse game between
bootleggers in hot rod Chevys and revenue officers intent on
confiscating their cargo, stock car racing is now the nation's
fastest growing sport. The 49ers of the University of North
Carolina at Charlotte are one of six university racing teams in the
Southeast intent on expanding the definition of the sport. By Joe
Drape.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-FALK-NBA (Undated) _ Characterized as a puppeteer by David
Stern, widely regarded as having a major influence on the actions
of the players union, the agent David Falk is seen by all as being
at the center of the NBA labor dispute. But what is his real
influence? And why does everybody hate him? By Mike Wise.
</P>
