<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
TODAY 
No bowl games today. But the alternative isn't the NFL in this
less-than-glamorous, regular-season closer that seems to typify
``Monday Night Football's'' luck this year. Try the NHL. NFL:
Pittsburgh at Jacksonville, Channel 7, 5:20 p.m.; NHL: Kings at
Phoenix, Fox Sports West, 6 p.m. 
TUESDAY 
Three bowl games today. But admit it: The college hoops look more
interesting, especially Jim Harrick's return to Pepperdine for a
night. Music City Bowl: Alabama vs. Virginia Tech, ESPN, 2 p.m.;
Micron PC Bowl: North Carolina State vs. Miami, 4:30 p.m., TBS;
Alamo Bowl: Kansas State vs. Purdue, ESPN, 5:30 p.m. College
basketball: Pete Newell Classic on Fox Sports West _ North Carolina
vs. Cal, 6 p.m., and Temple vs. Stanford, 8:30 p.m. Also: Rhode
Island at Pepperdine, FSW2, 5 p.m. and Loyola Marymount at UCLA,
FSW2, 7:30 p.m. 
WEDNESDAY 
Two bowl games today. Any real humanitarian would schedule just one
instead. Humanitarian Bowl: Idaho vs. Southern Miss, ESPN2, noon;
Holiday Bowl: Arizona vs. Nebraska, ESPN, 5 p.m. 
THURSDAY 
Four bowl games today. Win or lose, USC fans will hop back on the
plane and be home in time to party like it's 1999. Sun Bowl: USC
vs. TCU, Channel 2, 11 a.m.; Liberty Bowl: BYU vs. Tulane, ESPN,
10:30 a.m.; Peach Bowl: Virginia vs. Georgia, ESPN, 2 p.m.;
Independence Bowl: Mississippi vs. Texas Tech, ESPN, 5:30 p.m. 
FRIDAY 
Only six New Year's Day games today? Has someone at the networks
finally wised up? And by the way, tape the Rose Bowl _ it's Keith
Jackson's last paid trip to Pasadena. Outback Bowl: Penn State vs.
Kentucky, ESPN, 8 a.m.; Gator Bowl: Georgia Tech vs. Notre Dame,
Channel 4, 9:30 a.m.; Citrus Bowl: Michigan vs. Arkansas, Channel
7, 10 a.m.; Cotton Bowl: Texas vs. Mississippi State, Channel 11,
10:30 a.m.; Rose Bowl: UCLA vs. Wisconsin, Channel 7, 1:30 p.m.;
Sugar Bowl: Ohio State vs. Texas A&AMP;M, Channel 7, 5:30 p.m. 
SATURDAY 
Next-to-last bowl game today. Orange you glad? And the first round
of the NFL playoffs begin. Orange Bowl: Syracuse vs. Florida,
Channel 7, 5 p.m. NFL wild-card playoffs: Buffalo at Miami, 9:30
a.m. and Arizona at Dallas, 1:05 p.m., both games on Channel 7. 
SUNDAY 
In a weekend break before the big bowl (for college fans), the NFL
eliminates four pretenders from the playoff picture _ after the
Raiders have already been dismissed. NFL wild-card playoffs: New
England at Jacksonville, Channel 2, 10 a.m.; Green Bay at San
Francisco, Channel 11, 1 p.m. 

